  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0dba \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0daf\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 600\u0d9a\u0dca - WHO",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "600 million global covid infections - WHO",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the latest data from the World Health Organization (WHO), the number of global Covid-19 cases has exceeded 600 million.",
        "As of Thursday, the World Health Organization reported 600,555,262 confirmed cases of Covid-19 globally, including 6,472,914 deaths.",
        "The United States has the highest number of confirmed cases and deaths, with more than 93.21 million cases and more than 1.03 million deaths. This is nearly 15% of the global total.",
        "The next highest totals were recorded in India and Brazil, with over 44 million and 34 million cases respectively, as well as 527,911 and 683,851 confirmed deaths.",
        "As far as WHO regional offices are concerned, Europe and America have so far reported more than 248 million and 175 million confirmed cases, with 2,077,355 and 2,817,530 deaths respectively. These two regions together account for more than 70% of the world's total confirmed cases and more than 75% of deaths.",
        "Although the number of new Covid-19 cases and deaths continues to decline weekly, the director-general of the World Health Organization said last week that the world had \"passed the tragic milestone of one million deaths so far this year.\"",
        "However, the global organizations that analyze the data in this regard have added that these infected figures and the number of deaths are much higher."
      ],
